<div class="row section version" id="dwn-mac"> <!-- Mac OS X Versions -->
  <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-xs-12">
    <h5 class="gray">Mac OS X Signatures</h5>

    <div class="panel-group" id="accordionMac">
      <div class="panel panel-link"> <!-- collapseClamxav-->
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordionMac" href="#collapseClamxav"><span class="red">ClamXav</span></a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseClamxav" class="panel-collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>ClamXav for Mac OS X is available for purchase on the Mac App Store. ClamXav can be set up as passive or
              active: scan only the files you tell it to or your entire hard drive. You can also choose to activate
              Sentry to monitor your hard drive and scan new files as they arrive.</p>

            <p>The ClamXav project was developed by Mark Allan.

            <p>

            <p>To learn more, visit <a class="red" href="http://www.clamxav.com/" target="_blank">www.clamxav.com</a>.
