<div class="row section tool" id="POP3"> <!-- POP3 -->
  <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
    <h5 class="gray">Post Office Protocol Tools</h5>

    <div class="panel-group">
      <div class="panel panel-link"> <!-- collapse20 -->
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse20">P3Scan | <em> clamscan</em></a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapse20" class="panel-collapse collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">P3Scan is a fullly-transparent proxy server for POP3-Clients. It runs on a Linux box
            with iptables (for port re-direction). It can be used to provide POP3 email scanning from the internet to
            any internal network and is ideal for helping protect your Other OS LAN from harm, especially when used in
            conjunction with a firewall and other Internet Proxy servers. P3Scan is designed to enable scanning of
            incoming email messages for Virus’s, Worms, Trojans, Spam (read as Un-solicited Bulk Email), and harmfull
            attachments. Because viewing HTML mail can enable a Spammer to validate an email address (by the email
            client automatically reaching out and touching the web host), it can also provide HTML stripping. P3Scan is
            a derived work of:[POP3VScan [pop3vscan]]. | get
            <a class="blue" href="http://p3scan.sourceforge.net/" target="_blank">P3Scan</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-1">&nbsp;</div>
